Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.16,0:22:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person may still have negative feelings.\NSo the person in level of courage is going to ask the boss for a raise, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.16,0:22:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,His stomach may still be in a knot.\NHe might be angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.16,0:22:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He might even feel hopeless that he's going to get the raise.\NHe might even be arrogant.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.16,0:22:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But now he has enough power to handle all that and be appropriate.\NSo he's able to face it and cope with it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.16,0:22:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and able to function in an effective way in the world.\NThat brings us to the next level,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.96,0:22:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,where now you see the energy field swings to the right,\Nthat which is positive, that which is aligned with the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.96,0:23:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the energy field jumps to 250,\Nand this one is called neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.96,0:23:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the emotion that goes with neutral is one of unattached, non-attachment,\Nso that it's okay if you get the job and it's okay if you don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.96,0:23:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The process going on in consciousness is we say the person is now released.\NThey're not attached to any particular outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.99,0:23:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They're no longer a victim.\NThe person now has a great deal more power.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.99,0:23:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we say no aversions, no attachments.\NThe person has no attachments and no aversions,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.99,0:23:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning that they are now above the solar plexus.\NUnattached, the downside of unattached can be detached or flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.79,0:23:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the upside of it can be the okayness of life,\Nso that if you don't get this job, you'll get another job.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.79,0:23:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person is no longer a victim.\NHe's no longer a leaf in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.79,0:24:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And the person's now feeling released\Nand therefore in a much better state, in a far more powerful state.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.18,0:24:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see the way that person sees the world is okay,\Nand the way they experience God is freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.18,0:24:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person then talks about,\Nyou know, going free, God as being freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.18,0:24:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And they talk about, you know, detachment and feeling released.\NThe next energy field above that is called willingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.91,0:24:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Willingness, you see, at 310 is far more powerful to the right.\NAnd the emotion of that is accompanied by the thoughts of yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.91,0:24:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Saying yes to life, to join, to agree, to commit, to align with.\NBecause now we have the introduction of intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.91,0:24:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So a person on the level of neutral, let's say,\Nyou say to them, would you like to go to a movie tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.14,0:24:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, well, it's okay if we go, and it's okay if we don't.\NI mean, that's not exactly enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.14,0:25:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not exactly aliveness.\NYou know, it's a long way from abundance yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.14,0:25:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And certainly far more comfortable than being down here.\NTo be detached feels more comfortable than being in fear or grief or apathy or anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.14,0:25:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is still a far cry from willing.\NYou know, waitress who perfunctorily,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.68,0:25:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay if she serves you, it's okay if she doesn't,\Nis different than the one who is willing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.68,0:25:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because she's now bringing her own aliveness,\Nher own intention to say yes, to commit and to agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.68,0:25:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And so real power then begins with this level here\Nbecause you've let go the resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.68,0:25:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So the beauty of neutral is that you've let go resisting things\Nand you have a lot more power.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.68,0:25:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But now you have to introduce a new energy to move up to 310, which is willingness.\NWhich moves us to the next field above that called acceptance.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.32,0:25:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Acceptance at 380 is a very powerful energy field.\NThat's the energy field of being capable, adequate and confident.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.32,0:26:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And at that level there's the beginning of a transformation in consciousness.\NAnd why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.32,0:26:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The transformation has to do with the person's re-owning\Nthat they are the source of their own happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.32,0:26:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That the power is within myself.\NAnd so a person on this level then,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.32,0:26:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the person that a big corporation that has a very big contract,\Nyou know, to get all of Europe or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.32,0:26:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,sends out a person on this level.\NBecause this person is realistic
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.32,0:26:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,in that they can admit their upside and they can admit their downside.\NSee, they're not into pride, which means denial,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.32,0:26:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,so they can allow for their weaknesses and their shortcomings.\NSo an executive on that level can say,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.32,0:26:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I don't do very well with that guy,\Nyou know, in Argentina,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.32,0:26:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, it'd be better if you sent Jake,\NI'm sure he'd get along better.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.32,0:26:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He can indicate where he's limited.\NAnd a person on a level of acceptance accepts how the world works,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.32,0:27:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,has stopped getting into a right and wrong about it\Nand therefore can deal with it effectively.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.32,0:27:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The transformation is because of the re-owning of one's own power.\NAnd a person on this level knows that no matter where you put him,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.32,0:27:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow he will create a circumstance that will create happiness.\NSo that person, if you drop them on a desert island
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.67,0:27:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you come back a year later,\Nyou'll find that he's, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.67,0:27:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,has a coconut farm going and has built a tree house\Nand has started a new family with a native girl
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.67,0:27:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and is teaching children French,\Nthe person makes out wherever they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.25,0:27:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the same would be, let's say, putting the person in jail.\NSo jail is a place, or prison is a place,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.25,0:27:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,where at the bottom of the rung you can commit suicide,\Nyou can go into depression and despair,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.25,0:27:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,or you could become enlightened\Nor write a great novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.25,0:27:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, some of the greatest works of literature ever written\Nhave been written in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.25,0:27:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So a person on this level then would say,\Nwow, I'm in prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.44,0:28:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,at least I got a chance to do what I've always wanted to do all my life,\Nand sits down and proceeds to write the great novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.44,0:28:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, on the destructive side, something like Mein Kampf, you know.\NHitler wrote Mein Kampf in prison
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.44,0:28:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and practically changed the face of Europe,\Nchanged the face of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.44,0:28:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the utilization then of opportunity,\Ncoming from this level,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.54,0:28:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,can be turned into turning lemons into lemonade.\NThat comes from a position, a way of being,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.54,0:28:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,a reowning of one's own power.\NThat leads to a certain easygoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.54,0:28:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So these people are easygoing.\NThey don't ruffle easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.24,0:28:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That reowning one's own power, then,\Nand recycling of the energy back from the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.24,0:28:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the constant reowning of that\Nthen moves the person up to an energy field of 500,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.24,0:28:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and we call that love.\NThis type of love is an energy field which is stable,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.75,0:28:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's called unconditional love.\NAnd the emotions that accompany this are
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.75,0:28:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to support,\Nto nurture, to honor all of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.75,0:29:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and forgiveness is part and parcel of it,\Nbecause the motivation there,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.75,0:29:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose there is to understand.\NSo the purpose down here, you see, is to win,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.75,0:29:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,or to make wrong.\NIt becomes a moralistic position.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.75,0:29:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This person up here is not interested in right and wrong.\NThis person is interested in understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.75,0:29:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we talked about the 12-step groups, such as AA,\Nwe characterized them as unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.26,0:29:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is different than what the world calls love.\NWhat the world calls love is something down in here
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.00,0:29:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which is an attachment.\NAs Solar Plexus says,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.00,0:29:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,sentimentalism, emotionalism.\NI can't live without you, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.00,0:29:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll kill myself if you leave me.\NI'll kill you if you leave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.00,0:29:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this.\NI'll die of loneliness if you walk out of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.00,0:29:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's out of this energy field here that you hear remarks like,\NI used to be in love with George, but I'm not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.00,0:30:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What that means is I never was in love with George,\Nbut I had a sentimentalism, an emotionalism, an attachment,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.00,0:30:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a mutual control and dependency,\Nand a lusting after,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.06,0:30:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and an ownership.\NThis kind of love is something that comes from within oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.06,0:30:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from an inner declaration,\Nit comes from an intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.06,0:30:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes from a realization of truth,\Nand it comes out as lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.06,0:30:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person from this energy field then\Nis loving towards all of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.06,0:30:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,whether the life is a little toad\Nor whether the life is standing in sort of a tough love situation
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.06,0:30:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for the good of someone else.\NIt nurtures and it supports life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.06,0:30:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the beginning of a revelation.\NAnd the brain enzyme changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.06,0:30:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got a column here for brain enzymes.\NThe brain enzyme changes at the beginning of the release of endorphins.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.06,0:30:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And the release of endorphins then opens millions of banks of neurons,\Nwhich up to this time have been sitting around
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.06,0:31:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,waiting for this energy field to activate them.\NAnd so the whole field of endorphins is the whole field of current research.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.83,0:31:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,At about 540 is the energy field of healing,\Nhealers, people that are touch healers
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.83,0:31:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,or thought healers,\Nthe various healing energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.83,0:31:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So 540 is the energy field of healing.\NAnd curiously enough, that's the energy field of the 12-step groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.83,0:31:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They come out at about 540.\NAnything that you put in a plus positive energy field of 540 begins to heal,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.96,0:31:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's a sick animal,\Nan emotionally sick human being,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.96,0:31:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,an addicted person, whatever.\NA plus energy field of 540 then is healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.96,0:31:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The...\NThere's a rise in the intensity of the energy field of aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.96,0:31:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we...\NWe look to be around those kind of people because they make us feel more alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.18,0:31:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They make us feel more alive.\NThey give out energy to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.18,0:32:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,These people down here are pulling energy from the field.\NPulling energy field because they're coming from lack.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.18,0:32:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming from a graspingness, a neediness.\NAnd so they tire us and...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.86,0:32:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When this person sits out in the waiting room, you see,\Nand the boss or secretary goes out,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.86,0:32:20.86,Default,,0,0,0,,she comes in, she tells the boss,\Nthere's a guy waiting for you out in front.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.86,0:32:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And with a little flick of the eyebrow, she indicates,\Nforget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.86,0:32:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She's already just gotten the energy field that he came from.\NWhen this person sits out in the waiting room,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.86,0:32:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,he's not going to wait long because they...\NThe secretary instantly gets who that person is and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.86,0:32:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,boss, you're running a little bit late.\NThere's a guy waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.86,0:32:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, she indicates by a flick of an eyebrow,\Nthis is somebody you don't want to keep.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.86,0:32:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is somebody you don't want to keep waiting.\NShe doesn't know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.86,0:32:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because she's picked up this energy field.\NSo it's a very powerful energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.27,0:32:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,At the bottom, you see...\NAt the bottom, these are situations of lose-lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.27,0:33:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody loses.\NYou lose and the people that become associated with you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.27,0:33:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in your life lose.\NAnd this point of view is one of losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.27,0:33:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So that the person says,\Neverywhere I look, there's a closed door.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.27,0:33:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If I do go this way, I'll lose.\NIf I go this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.27,0:33:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is seen as a losing proposition.\NThe people in the middle look at life as win-lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.37,0:33:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of their pridefulness,\Nout of that polarization of angriness,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.37,0:33:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because they see the world as competition and conflict.\NThese people live in a world of win-lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.37,0:33:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If I win, therefore you lose.\NTherefore, they have endless unconscious fears of retaliation
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.37,0:33:41.37,Default,,0,0,0,,because they look at success as vanquishing\Nand then expect retaliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.37,0:33:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you beat somebody in this game,\Nyou can't really win because, after all,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.37,0:33:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he's got friends that may come looking for you someday.\NSo you can never relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.37,0:33:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,These people up here conceptualize and hold life\Nas a win-win situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.37,0:33:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So that when I win, you win.\NEverybody in the family wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.37,0:34:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The company wins.\NSo the more money the company makes,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.37,0:34:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the better for the employees.\NYou know, everybody tends to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.53,0:34:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are win-win situations.\NSo as we...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.53,0:34:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,just as we avoid these people down here\Nand tolerate these people in here,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.53,0:34:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,these people are sought.\NSo these people don't have to look for jobs
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.53,0:34:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,or look for invitations\Nor look for relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.53,0:34:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,People seek them out.\NPeople call them up and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.53,0:34:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you like to work for us?\NWouldn't you like to be vice president of marketing for our company?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.53,0:34:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So people seek you out.\NWouldn't you like to come to our party?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.53,0:34:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you like to go to bed with me?\NEt cetera, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.53,0:34:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,These people are sought.\NAnd so it comes out of the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.53,0:34:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,field.\NAnd as we move up towards 540,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.53,0:34:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,we see there's an inner joy.\NNot an emotionalism coming out of the solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.53,0:34:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,like you just won the ball game\Njumping up and down,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.53,0:34:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but a quiet inner knowingness\Nis beginning to take place now
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.53,0:34:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,because at this energy field of revelation,\None connects within oneself
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.53,0:35:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,with something rock-like,\Nsomething that is always there.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.53,0:35:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And so this is the beginning\Nof the transfiguration of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.53,0:35:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see the beginning\Nof an inner serenity
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.53,0:35:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the opening of compassion.\NAnd at 560,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.53,0:35:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that reaches actually an ecstasy,\Nan inner exquisite knowingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.53,0:35:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a transfiguration of consciousness\Nwhich is going to be leading up to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.53,0:35:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in states really of illumination\Nas we get close to 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.82,0:35:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,This energy field of compassion\Nis one which one can elect.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.82,0:35:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,There are several places one can elect.\NOne certainly has a choice here
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.82,0:35:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell the truth\Nand bring oneself up to this energy field here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.82,0:35:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,One can make a commitment\Nto lovingness as a way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.82,0:35:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So this requires no belief in God\Nor any theological, spiritual system.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.82,0:35:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That commitment to lovingness,\Nto that which nurtures and supports life
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.82,0:36:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,in all of its expressions.\NIt sees that which is divine in all things
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.82,0:36:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,as it moves up to an even higher level\Nwhere it begins to see the perfection of all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.62,0:36:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Compassion then is a way of knowing,\Na way of looking into the hearts of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.62,0:36:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because of the release of endorphins\Nhere at this level of revelation,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.62,0:36:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of transfiguration,\Nthere comes that knowing,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.62,0:36:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the separation between one self as an individual\Nand another self as an individual
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.62,0:36:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to break down.\NAnd there's almost like the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.62,0:36:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of a oneness of the heart,\Na knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.62,0:36:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a thinkingness, but a knowingness.\NDifferent than thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.65,0:36:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something we're missing on the board here\Nand that is the energy fields in here
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.65,0:36:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because we don't have enough room\Nto put it on the blackboard,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.65,0:36:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of the four hundreds.\NSee, the four hundreds are the level of mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.65,0:37:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of intellect, of thinkingness,\Nof the process going on in consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.65,0:37:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of conceptualization.\NConceptualization.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.65,0:37:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NSo this is mind in the four hundreds,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.13,0:37:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness, intellect, etc.\NAnd above that is heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.13,0:37:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the statement that says\Nthat the thing that differentiates man from the animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.13,0:37:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the thing that makes the man the highest of all things\Nis his intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.13,0:37:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't come out here correctly.\NIt's man's heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.13,0:37:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the heart you see is higher than the head.\NThe heart, which doesn't think, just knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.13,0:37:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So at this energy field,\Nis knowingness without the necessity for thinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.13,0:37:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,See, and the god of mind,\Nthe god of the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.13,0:37:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is intelligence.\NAnd the worship of intelligence then,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.13,0:37:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,being in the four hundreds,\Nis certainly higher than these
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.13,0:37:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of demonic levels down below.\NBut it is still a far cry from
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.13,0:38:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,those states of the full opening of the heart.\NSo that love, the energy field of heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.13,0:38:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then begins about here\Nand goes up to infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.13,0:38:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So love, we begin to detect that at five hundred,\Nwhich is the energy field of happiness, by the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.16,0:38:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,begins at five hundred.\NBut then that expands up into infinity
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.16,0:38:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,through the six hundred, seven hundred, eight hundred,\Nup to a thousand and beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.16,0:38:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So these are the beginning of the energy field,\Nbut by no means the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.16,0:38:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the beginning and it goes on to infinity.\NThis level of revelation then opens our way
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.74,0:38:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to transfiguration and this compassion\Nwhich leads to ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.74,0:38:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And leads up to the states close to six hundred,\Nwhich are states of bliss,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.74,0:38:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of states of illumination\Nand enlightenment and experientially
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.74,0:38:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,they are often accompanied by feelings of light.\NLight, the room lit up.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.74,0:38:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When Bill Wilson, for instance,\Nhad his spiritual experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.74,0:39:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,he said the room lit up by the infinite presence.\NAnd that was the beginning of the approach
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.74,0:39:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of that energy field of six hundred.\NThe energy field is up here called bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.74,0:39:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, that was very important in our talk on addiction\Nbecause we said that the energy field of bliss
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.74,0:39:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,transforms the person's life.\NThe person who falls into samadhi by accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.74,0:39:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,goes into a transcendental state.\NSo six hundred and up are transcendental states.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.74,0:39:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually that person's life is changed thereafter.\NPeople who have near-death experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.74,0:39:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and experience those energy fields over six hundred\Nexperience the presence of their own higher self,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.74,0:39:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the conscious awareness of one solar angel.\NThose are levels beyond which
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.74,0:39:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,then go on up to infinity\Nand the various world famous spiritual teachers
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.74,0:39:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's a whole subject in itself,\Nthe subject of what goes on in the six hundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.74,0:39:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We can say roughly that\Nthe beginning of the energy field of the Christ and the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.74,0:39:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,is around seven hundred and fifty to eight hundred\Nand then goes from there on up to infinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.74,0:40:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the levels which have such enormous power\Nthat we call them avatars.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.74,0:40:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,An avatar in three years of his ministry\Nthe Christ totally transformed and changed the consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.74,0:40:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of all mankind for thousands of years to come.\NTransformed our life on the horizontal plane
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.15,0:40:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as the vertical.\NAnd so those are fields of enormous power.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.22,0:40:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least it gives us an idea now\Nwhere all this fits together.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.22,0:40:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And we said that this energy field here\Ncan be experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.38,0:40:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,by removing one's experience of these things.\NIt's like the sun is always shining
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.38,0:40:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and these energy fields here are like the clouds.\NAnd as we remove the clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.38,0:40:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we experience the sun which is always shining.\NAnd in the talk on addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.47,0:40:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we made a very precise point\Nthat it's not the removal of the clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.47,0:40:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that causes the sun to shine\Nwhich is what the addicted person begins to think.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.47,0:41:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now people who get addicted to anything\Nthinking that because of the left brain
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.47,0:41:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,type of thinking linear causes\Ncausality that A causes B causes C.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.60,0:41:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The removal of this.\NSo the whole purpose of spiritual work then
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.60,0:41:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is the removal of these clouds\Nso that one experiences the shining forth
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.60,0:41:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of the self with a capital S\Nwhich is at the top of the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.59,0:41:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,These energy fields then are so powerful\Nthey dominate our perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.59,0:41:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They're really portholes out of which we see the world.\NAnd we often hear it said that this is really
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.59,0:41:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,just a world of mirrors.\NThat all we're experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.59,0:41:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is our own energy field\Ncontrolling our perception and our experiencing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.59,0:41:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's look at that then.\NLet's look at perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.59,0:41:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at the view of the world\Nand the view of life
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.59,0:41:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,as it comes out of these various energy fields.\NAs we said in the beginning, guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.33,0:41:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that self-hatred, that destructive energy field\Nsees a world of sin and suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.42,0:42:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore that person walking down the street\Nlooks around and all that person sees is suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.42,0:42:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And when they open the newspaper\Nwhat they see is the endless suffering of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.42,0:42:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who is in this energy field here\Nof hopelessness and despair
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.06,0:42:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,literally sees a hopeless world.\NAnd when he opens the newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.06,0:42:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,he notices the hopeless condition of mankind\Nthe endless wars, the endless poverty,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.06,0:42:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the endless crime.\NAnd so actually experiences perceptually,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.22,0:42:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,visually, auditorily, through all the senses\Nexperiences a world
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.22,0:42:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of hopelessness.\NSo what kind of a God could be the God
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.51,0:42:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of a hopeless world as we said\Nthis is God is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.51,0:42:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in grief, regret and loss and despondency\Nthat dispirited state
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.74,0:42:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of the loss of the will to live\Nwalks down the street and sees this as a sad world.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.77,0:43:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is what is actually experienced\Nand you know yourself if you're in a sad state
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.77,0:43:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,when you walk down the street\Nyou see the children and you think
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.77,0:43:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,how sad.\NYou know you look at the old people
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.77,0:43:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and you think how sad.\NYou look at the buildings
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.77,0:43:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you look at mankind's condition\Nand you think how sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.77,0:43:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I said you open the newspaper\Nand you see how sad is life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.77,0:43:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's your own energy field coloring everything.\NSo these are like colored glasses
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.77,0:43:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and we put them on\Nand we then experience everything
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.77,0:43:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as being colored by this energy field.\NThe person in fear as we well know
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.57,0:43:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,sees this as a threatening world\Na frightening world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.57,0:43:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Constant jeopardy.\NSo he sees it as a world of danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.57,0:43:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person walking down the street\Nin that energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.57,0:43:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,sees danger everywhere.\NSees that you could break your ankle here
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.57,0:43:51.57,Default,,0,0,0,,break your ankle there.\NThey cover everything with insurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.57,0:43:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They see the threat\Nmuggers everywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.57,0:43:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and rapers under the bed.\NAnd of course when they open the newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.57,0:44:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,they see the frightening conditions of all of life.\NThe jeopardy, the danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.57,0:44:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And they live in their house\Nthey lock their car
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.57,0:44:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and their own garage\Nand then they lock the garage
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.57,0:44:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which is in their house which is locked\Nwhich is in their yard which is locked
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.57,0:44:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,which is in a neighborhood\Nwhich has never had a robbery yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.57,0:44:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet the fear goes on you see.\NSo having more police doesn't really help
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.57,0:44:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,because where are the police going to be\Nwhen your house is robbed?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.57,0:44:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You know where they're going to be.\NThey're going to be at the other end of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.57,0:44:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So it doesn't help.\NSo trying to change the world then
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.82,0:44:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't really assuage it\Nbecause it's coming from one's own energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.82,0:44:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The field above that\Ndesiringness then sees this
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.78,0:44:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as a frustrating world of endless wantingness.\NAnd so the person coming from this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.78,0:44:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of wantingness\Nthis solar plexus fixation
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.78,0:44:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as they walk down the street\Nthey see all the things they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.78,0:44:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They see the cars they want\Nthe beauty that they want
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.78,0:44:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the status, the positions\Nthe buildings they want.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.78,0:45:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So because the world is therefore frustrating\Nbecause of their endless wantingness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.78,0:45:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,which can never be satisfied.\NSo that's the multi-millionaire
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.78,0:45:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,whose fingernails grow long\Nand their hair grows long
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.78,0:45:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and they get paranoid and weird\Nas they get older.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.78,0:45:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,More and more millions of dollars\Ndoesn't satisfy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.78,0:45:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that they have 50 million doesn't help\Nbecause the desiring, the wanting
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.78,0:45:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,for more power.\NSo these are fields then
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.78,0:45:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that cannot be satisfied\Nand this frustration leads to anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.78,0:45:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So the angry world then sees\Nthe angry person then sees
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.78,0:45:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,a competitive world\Na world of conflict, of war
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.78,0:45:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of me against you.\NThe person into this competitive view of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.78,0:45:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,looks out in the woods\Nand thinks that the tall trees are competing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.78,0:45:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,with the small trees for the sunlight.\NAs you can see this is a conception
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.82,0:45:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,then projected on to a field\Nwhere there is no such thing as competition
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.82,0:45:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,even going on.\NAnd so that person lives in a world
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.82,0:46:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of endless possibility of war\Nand conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.82,0:46:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and they see everything as competition\Nnot as cooperation
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.82,0:46:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which a person up here would see.\NThe person who is into pride
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.82,0:46:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,sees this as a world of status\Nand so that person walking down the same street
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.82,0:46:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,sees the Gucci shoes\Nsees the name tags
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.82,0:46:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and sees the labels\Nsees the status
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.82,0:46:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't see grief or any of this at all\Nonly sees the kind of car they would want
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.82,0:46:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the kind of building they would like to live\Nthey classify everything in terms of status
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.82,0:46:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and so positionality\Nthey are preoccupied with positionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.82,0:46:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens when you get to the level of truth\Nthe level of courage
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.82,0:46:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the world suddenly appears\Nas a place of opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.82,0:46:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The world is an exciting challenging place\Nan opportunity for growth and expansion
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.82,0:46:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that person opens the newspaper\Nand sees the endless opportunities
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.82,0:46:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for man to grow\Nto meet these challenges
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.82,0:46:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to go beyond them\Nto learn in the process
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.82,0:47:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and so that person is excited about life.\NAs we move up to neutral then
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.23,0:47:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we move into a world of okayness\Nbecause this person is detached
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.23,0:47:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,unattached\Nrather non-attached
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.23,0:47:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,everything sort of becomes okay\Nand you start moving into an easy going view of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.23,0:47:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the person begins to say\Nwell that's human nature
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.23,0:47:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the way it is\Nit's serving some kind of an ultimate purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.23,0:47:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who moves into willingness\Nnow for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.30,0:47:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to experience this as a friendly world\Nand that person walking down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.30,0:47:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,sees the endless friendlinesses that go on\Nhow friendly this universe is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.30,0:47:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what you have\Nlike you pull your nose in a hanky
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.30,0:47:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a waste basket right there\Nthe world is harmonious
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.30,0:47:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and friendly and supportive.\NThe person on the level of acceptance then
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.36,0:47:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,really experiences that harmony of life\Nbegins to experience what Jung calls synchronicity
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.36,0:47:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how everything just sort of flows together\Nand begins to experience a world of cooperation
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.36,0:48:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because he's holding cooperation\Nas his own energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.36,0:48:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,he experiences life as cooperative.\NThis person as he moves into lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.39,0:48:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to experience the lovingness\Nand the endless loving support
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.39,0:48:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the universality of that loving energy in the universe.\NThe person moving up towards states of illumination
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.39,0:48:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to experience the incredible beauty\Nand perfection of life
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.39,0:48:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the absolute perfection of creation\Nand as he moves up towards the highest energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.39,0:48:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,he experiences actually the divine essence\Nand nature of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.39,0:48:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The incredible beauty of all things\Nnot aesthetic beauty which is pleasing to the senses
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.39,0:48:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but the intrinsic beauty\Nwhich when you walk down an alley
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.39,0:48:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,which to the eye of the unenlightened would look ugly\Nexperiences the incredible perfection and beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.39,0:48:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of the aliveness of life\Nbegins to see all of life as a rose unfolding
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.39,0:48:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so he doesn't see imperfection\Nsees process
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.39,0:49:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that person there instead of being wrong\Nis in the unfoldment
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.39,0:49:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,sees all of the universe as the unfoldment of that perfection.\NSo what kind of a God can one envision
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.81,0:49:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,from these various energy fields then?\NAs we said this person here
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.81,0:49:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,envisions a God who is the ultimate destroyer\Nand actually the ultimate enemy and hater of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.81,0:49:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the ultimate of hatred.\NTo throw your eternal soul into hell forever
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.38,0:49:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the ultimate act of hate.\NThe person in apathy and hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.80,0:49:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,experiences God as dead.\NThe person who is in this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.80,0:49:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes says I believe in God\Nbut I feel he wouldn't have anything to do with me
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.80,0:49:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because I am just a worm, worthless.\NI am so worthless that God would have nothing to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.80,0:49:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who lives in fear\Nsees a punitive, frightening, terrifying God.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.80,0:49:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who lives in frustration\Nfeels separated from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.93,0:50:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the God who constantly whispers.\NThat's the God who constantly withholds from you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.93,0:50:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that which would allow you to be happy.\NAnd therefore he is actually acting in a very hostile manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.93,0:50:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The person in anger expects, of course,\Na retaliatory, punishing God.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.93,0:50:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And because these things go together\Nwe then get the God who is really demonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.93,0:50:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The God who really hates you.\NWho threatens to throw you into hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.93,0:50:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate destroyer, the punisher.\NThe God who is vengeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.93,0:50:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The God who is jealous.\NSo we get a depiction of a God who is fitfully jealous
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.93,0:50:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and given to emotional extremes of destructiveness.\NThese are all coming out, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.93,0:50:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of a field of consciousness\Nhaving no basis in reality whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.93,0:50:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When we get up to here, the level of pride\Nwe can have two directions to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.06,0:50:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the arrogance.\NBecause of the inflated ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.06,0:50:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We can have, on the one hand, atheism\Nor on the other side, the zealot.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.06,0:51:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The bigot. The one who knows.\NSo these are people who have the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.06,0:51:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer is coming out of intellectual arrogance.\NAs we move up to courage, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.38,0:51:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the level of truth,\Nwhat kind of God do we have?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.38,0:51:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We have God of a question mark.\NFor the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.38,0:51:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're now hitting the level of truth,\Nwe have an open mind and the person says,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.38,0:51:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, I really don't know about God.\NIt's only hearsay.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.38,0:51:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All that I've read, all that I've heard,\Nall that religion teaches
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.44,0:51:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is really other people's experience\Nin times and places.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.44,0:51:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the witness stand, frankly,\NI would have to say, I don't know anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.44,0:51:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the question mark, the spiritual seeking,\Nreally begins at this level.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.44,0:51:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The person says, I of my own self\Nwould like to know what is the truth of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.44,0:51:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you move into the God of one's own inner experience.\NThe God of one's own understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.27,0:51:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,As you move up to this level of neutral, then,\Nyou begin to experience a world of okayness
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.27,0:52:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and you experience, as we said before,\NGod as freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.27,0:52:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to experience that there is no punitive,\Nhateful, negative God at all
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.27,0:52:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because you've moved out of those energy fields.\NThere's a God of absolute, infinite freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.27,0:52:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to expand, to explore, to become,\Nto fulfill one's potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.34,0:52:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As we move up to the willingness, friendly level,\Nwe begin to experience God as something
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.34,0:52:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that is perhaps promising and hopeful.\NSomething that is now positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.34,0:52:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here it was negative.\NHere it opens to openness and freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.34,0:52:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But now it's beginning to look positive.\NAnd the person on this level here,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.34,0:52:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing life as harmony,\Nrealizes God is the ultimate merciful.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.34,0:52:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The ultimate, that which is all forgiving\Nand all merciful.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.37,0:52:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And the person in lovingness, then,\Nbegins to experience the God of unconditional love.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.37,0:52:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The ever presence of the love of God\Nas the source of one's happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.37,0:52:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and the source of life.\NAs we move into joy and the awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.37,0:53:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of beauty and perfection\Nand the divine essence of all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.37,0:53:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The oneness of God.\NThe oneness, the unity.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.37,0:53:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally we move to the top.\NGod as beingness, isness, the reality, the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.37,0:53:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is.\NThat which is nameless.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.37,0:53:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And one realizes that one is at one with that\Nas one goes into 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.37,0:53:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We now have a context\Nwhich will give a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.37,0:53:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,background, a way to hold now\Nand to see our spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.37,0:53:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,from a different perspective.\NTo see healing from a different perspective.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.37,0:53:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How to approach that\Ngreat enigma called the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.94,0:53:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We see now that\Nthis energy field of 540 and up,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.94,0:53:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the fields of compassion.\NWe're interested in compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.94,0:53:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And people in spiritual work are generally\Nperfecting.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.94,0:53:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They're coming from the 400s\Nwhere they have learningness,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.94,0:54:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge with a small k about spiritual matters.\NPutting them into effect
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.94,0:54:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying to perfect the 500s.\NOf course the miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.94,0:54:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the 12-step groups,\Na great many are concerned with
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.94,0:54:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfecting of the capacity to love.\NAnd we move up to a certain way then
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.01,0:54:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of viewing what the world calls the ego then.\NIf we, you see money in and of itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.04,0:54:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,let's take an example of money.\NMoney, wealth, power, sexuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.04,0:54:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,worldly success is all around 200.\NRemember in that movie Lost Horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.17,0:54:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where the hero falls into Shangri-La\Nwhich calibrates at about 625.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.17,0:54:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He comes back into the world of doingness.\NThis is the world of doingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.17,0:54:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And he no longer finds satisfaction\Nbecause he has experienced something higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.42,0:54:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You see at the bottom of the box here,\Nthis is the world of havingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.42,0:54:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what you have that counts.\NAnd people, status,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.42,0:55:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,etc. comes from what you have.\NIn the middle of the box,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.42,0:55:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the world of doingness.\NAt the bottom they want to know what you have
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.42,0:55:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and they rate you on what you have.\NThe world of doingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.42,0:55:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they want to know what you do in the world.\NWhat do you do there?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.42,0:55:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what position,\Nwhat is your function?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.42,0:55:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Havingness is no longer impressive.\NDown here at Cadillac it's very impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.42,0:55:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it's no longer so impressive\Nbecause everybody knows if you do plenty,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.42,0:55:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,like work seven days a week and two jobs,\Nthat you can have all you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.42,0:55:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So havingness then no longer has status.\NDoingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.42,0:55:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you move towards the top of the box,\Nit's not what you have,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.42,0:55:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not what you do,\Nit's what you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.42,0:55:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it's what you have become.\NPeople seek you out now
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.42,0:55:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for what you have become,\Nwhat you have,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.42,0:55:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth that you have owned about yourself.\NAnd so we seek those people
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.42,0:55:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because of what they are.\NWe don't even care what they have.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.42,0:55:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've known people like that for many years\Nand I never have known what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.42,0:56:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't know what they do.\NBut what they are is what is interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.42,0:56:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and why we seek their company.\NSo, utilizing this knowledge then,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.97,0:56:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we have an understanding of many things.\NThe way to heal the small self then
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.06,0:56:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is not to come from a polarized right-wrong position,\Na make-wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.06,0:56:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which makes it our enemy\Nand gives it energy and power,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.06,0:56:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but to come from a loving compassion,\Nto see the intrinsic,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.06,0:56:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the intrinsic innocence.\NBecause within this here,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.06,0:56:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,what you see is the innocence of the child.\NYou see the innocence of the child's consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.06,0:56:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you see the programming that comes in.\NIt's because of the child's lovingness and trustiness
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.06,0:56:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is so programmable.\NAnd you begin to see the innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.06,0:56:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,even within that which is most hateful.\NOut of one's compassion then,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.10,0:56:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to see into the hearts of things,\None sees the intrinsic innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.10,0:56:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,even within the ego.\NAnd so, how does it get healed then?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.10,0:57:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets healed out of compassion.\NIt gets loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.10,0:57:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We love our humanness.\NInstead of condemning it now,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.10,0:57:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we say,\NI see the necessity of that at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.10,0:57:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance,\Ninstead of being ashamed of anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.10,0:57:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred,\Nwe say to ourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.10,0:57:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,well, that being angry was necessary at that time.\NBecause a person who's never hated
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.10,0:57:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,will never move up to love, will they?\NBecause they've never cared that much about love,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.10,0:57:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,life.\NIf you don't care enough about life
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.10,0:57:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to have ever gotten angry\Nand actually hated,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.10,0:57:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,then you would be down here in apathy.\NSo we look at our humanness then
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.10,0:57:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of forgiveness,\Nfrom compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.10,0:57:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And we love it.\NWe hold it within our greatness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.10,0:57:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And we look at our smallness\Nlike we look at the child.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.10,0:57:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And we begin to heal it through understanding,\Nthrough compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.10,0:57:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we do, you see,\Nwe're pulling forth a very powerful energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.10,0:57:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,a healing energy field.\NWhen we look at ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.10,0:58:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from compassion and from lovingness,\Nwe begin to heal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.10,0:58:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course we know\Nthat which we forgive in others
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.10,0:58:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is forgiven within ourself.\NThat which we forgive in ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.10,0:58:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears from our perception of the world.\NSo our perception of the world begins to shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.10,0:58:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we hit the level of 600,\Nwe begin to experience a world
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.10,0:58:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which is totally different.\NI always say,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.10,0:58:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,movie A is replaced by movie B.\NIt's like you're putting on different colored glasses
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.10,0:58:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and now it looks the same\Nbut it's experienced totally differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.13,0:58:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that's the purpose of this map of consciousness,\Nto create a context
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.13,0:58:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which merely experiencing it,\Nmerely seeing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.13,0:58:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,opens whole new avenues.\NWhole new avenues begin to just open up automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.13,0:58:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And our intention,\Nour intention now is facilitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.13,0:58:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Our capacity to heal ourself\Nand to heal others,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.13,0:58:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the fulfillment of our own potential,\Nas we see ourself move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.13,0:58:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in our own realization of the truth.
